            . I <rs id="t18220220-122-viclabel662" type="occupation">keep a public-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220220-122-victim1206 t18220220-122-viclabel662"></join>, in <placeName id="t18220220-122-crimeloc663">Mapleton-place, Burton-crescent</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220220-122-crimeloc663" type="placeName" value="Mapleton-place, Burton-crescent"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220220-122-crimeloc663" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220220-122-off660 t18220220-122-crimeloc663"></join>. I let the prisoner a furnished room nine months ago, at 5 s. a week; he was four months with me, and went out after breakfast, on the 29th of October, saying he would return in five minutes, but never did; he left his room locked. I got it open, and missed the articles stated in the indictment.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did you not lend me the books - A. I lent him one - he conducted himself well - the things were entirely for his own private use.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220220-122-person1208">
